President Donald Trump issued a proclamation declaring April 2017 as National Financial Capability Month. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of empowering Americans to make independent financial decisions and informed choices in order to build wealth and pursue the American Dream. It highlights the challenges faced by many Americans, such as lack of emergency funds, insufficient savings for college, and concerns about retirement savings. The proclamation calls for the creation and implementation of innovative financial education curriculums to address these challenges and improve financial literacy. President Trump encourages all Americans to engage in activities that enhance their understanding of important financial decisions.